<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="549" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[341,455,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Stapecolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[341,455,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Stapecolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[462,567,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[462,567,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is proposed based on the clade H (
<figureCitation box="[956,1020,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,599,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1437,591,1156]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Relationships of the clade F (Herrichela clade of Ochlerini), modified from Garbelotto et al. (2013). In red, Stapecolis gen. nov.; in blue its sister group." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265423/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[1008,1020,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) of the phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1305,1436,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Herrichella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1436,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Herrichella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (
<bibRefCitation author="Garbelotto" box="[226,493,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" refString="Garbelotto, T. A., Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J. (2013) Cladistics and revision of Alitocoris with considerations on the phylogeny of the Herrichella clade (Hemiptera, Pentatomidae, Discocephalinae, Ochlerini). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 168, 452 - 472. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12032" type="journal article" year="2013">
Garbelotto 
<emphasis box="[357,423,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">et. al.</emphasis>
<number box="[432,493,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is supported by 
<number box="[825,853,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="10.0">10</number>
synapomorphies, including both somatic and male genital morphology; the following six are highlighted because they are also diagnostic characters: the anterolateral margins of pronotum crenulated, and the pygophore structures—dorsal rim with 
<number box="[1050,1062,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[1083,1095,296,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
expansions laterad to segment X; apex of the foliaceus expansions of the inferior layer of ventral rim with a small spinose carina; the absence of lobular expansions on superior layer of ventral rim; presence of subrectangular expansions below the ventral opening of ventral rim; and the subrectangular ventral opening of pygophore.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
Although only the presence of the spinose carina apical on the foliaceus expansions is unique in Ochlerini, the closely related genera (
<figureCitation box="[427,496,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,599,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1437,591,1156]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Relationships of the clade F (Herrichela clade of Ochlerini), modified from Garbelotto et al. (2013). In red, Stapecolis gen. nov.; in blue its sister group." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265423/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[484,496,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) have different states for the characters listed above, e.g. dorsal rim with 
<number box="[1392,1406,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[1422,1436,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2.0">2</number>
expansions laterad to segment X, the presence of lobular expansions on superior layer of ventral rim, and the ventral opening of pygophore not subrectangular (varying in each genera—see 
<bibRefCitation author="Garbelotto" box="[1033,1275,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" refString="Garbelotto, T. A., Campos, L. A. &amp; Grazia, J. (2011) A new synonymy in Alitocoris Sailer (Hemiptera, Pentatomidae, Discocephalinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 55 (1), 138 - 140. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262011000100023" type="journal article" year="2011">
Garbelotto 
<emphasis box="[1159,1215,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1221,1275,548,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
—figs 
<number box="[1352,1365,548,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="3.0">3</number>
–4, 7– 
<number box="[151,167,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="8.0">8</number>
; 
<number box="[179,234,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2013.0">2013</number>
—fig 
<number box="[300,315,584,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="9.0">9</number>
B; 
<number box="[347,403,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="2014.0">2014</number>
—figs 5, 8). Besides the synapomorphies, 
<taxonomicName box="[874,988,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Stapecolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[874,988,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Stapecolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[995,1099,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[995,1099,583,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has other particularities in the female genitalia as the gonocoxites 
<number box="[551,565,620,644]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="8.0">8</number>
with calluses on disc closer to its posterior margin and this projected over the laterotergites 
<number box="[303,319,656,680]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="9.0">9</number>
, and the yellow maculae on corium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
The sister-group of 
<taxonomicName box="[425,539,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Stapecolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[425,539,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Stapecolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,654,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[547,654,692,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is the clade I (
<figureCitation box="[826,892,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,599,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1437,591,1156]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Relationships of the clade F (Herrichela clade of Ochlerini), modified from Garbelotto et al. (2013). In red, Stapecolis gen. nov.; in blue its sister group." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265423/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[880,892,692,716]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) that includes 
<taxonomicName authority="Sailer" authorityName="Sailer" box="[1065,1362,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Alitocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1288,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Alitocoris brunneus</emphasis>
Sailer
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">sedis mutabilis</emphasis>
) and other two new species (to be described elsewere). Species of clade I are supported by female characters: the sutural margins of gonocoxites 
<number box="[682,696,764,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="8.0">8</number>
tumescent and its callosities projected to the lateral angles—two characters states absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[454,568,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Stapecolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[454,568,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">Stapecolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[576,683,799,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[576,683,799,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. This sister-group relationship (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1113,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1178,1200]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,599,1149]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1437,591,1156]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Relationships of the clade F (Herrichela clade of Ochlerini), modified from Garbelotto et al. (2013). In red, Stapecolis gen. nov.; in blue its sister group." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265423/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[1101,1113,800,824]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) is supported by the second antennal segment shorter than the first and the presence of a carina on gonocoxites 
<number box="[1082,1099,836,860]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" value="9.0">9</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,649,943,970]" box="[151,649,943,970]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,649,943,970]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" reason="1">
